    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't know if \"changes\" are even possible at this point. it's not like i'm just stuck in a rut or something. it feels more permanent than that. the person in those photos had a spark, a direction... they were alive. whatever is left of me now is just... empty. it's exhausting to keep dragging this heavy, hollow thing around every day. it doesn't feel like i'm living, i'm just occupying space. it's like i'm waiting for something to finally catch up to the fact that i'm already gone.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
